</simplesect>
<anchor id="http__connector_8h_1http_connector"/> <simplesect kind="par"><title>Detailed Description </title><para>AXO devices uses the HTTPS application layer protocol for the transmission of raw and displacement data to the remote webserver. See details of <ulink url="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/HTTP">HTTP</ulink> and <ulink url="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/HTTP">HTTPS</ulink> in wikipedia. For the data transmission HTTP POST is used. <linebreak/>
 The data to be transferred consists of the following parts:<itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>The HTTP POST header</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>The raw data header (first frame)<itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>IMEI</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>timestamp</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>total number of data samples</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Type of data (Raw or Displacement)</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>The x, y and z raw data samples (in the following frames)</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>OR the displacement data (in the following frames)</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>The SHA1 checksum (last frame) <linebreak/>
 See also message sequence chart in section <ref refid="_m_s_c_1SectionRawData" kindref="member">Raw Data Transmission</ref>. For SHA1 hash calculation the HTTP connector class uses the <ulink url="https://www.trustedfirmware.org/projects/mbed-tls/">mbedtls crypto library</ulink>.</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
</simplesect>
<simplesect kind="remark"><para>This source code is confidential and proprietary information of AXO Track GmbH, Berlin. You may not disclose, copy, or distribute this source code or any part thereof without the explicit permission of AXO Track GmbH, Berlin. </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
